---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-19";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Cookie policy — PDF Tools"
	description="What cookies pdf.oriz.in uses."
	canonical="/legal/cookies"
>
	<section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-blue-50/30 border-b border-gray-200/60">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
			<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2">
				<a href="/" class="hover:text-gray-900">PDF Tools</a> /
				<a href="/legal/" class="hover:text-gray-900">Legal</a> / Cookies
			</p>
			<h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight mb-2">
				Cookie policy
			</h1>
			<p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Last updated: {updated}</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 prose prose-gray max-w-none">
		<p>
			pdf.oriz.in uses the smallest set of cookies and storage we can get away with.
		</p>

		<h2>What we set</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Theme + accent</strong> — <code>localStorage</code> keys
				<code>oriz:theme</code> and <code>oriz:accent</code> remember your
				preference between visits. No tracking.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Auth session</strong> — when you sign in, Firebase Authentication
				sets cookies on <code>auth.oriz.in</code> so you stay logged in across
				every <code>*.oriz.in</code> site. These are first-party and essential.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Tool preferences</strong> — recently-used tools and
				per-tool defaults are stored in your browser's <code>localStorage</code>
				on this device only.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Third parties</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Cloudflare</strong> may set anti-abuse cookies (Turnstile, bot
				management). These are essential for site availability.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Google AdSense</strong> (once approved) may set advertising
				cookies. The consent banner lets you opt out per-purpose.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Opting out</h2>
		<p>
			You can clear localStorage and cookies for any oriz domain from your
			browser's site-data settings. Theme and auth will reset to defaults.
		</p>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>
